## Theory

For an isolated system of two bodies, conservation of momentum states:

$$m_1 v_{1i} + m_2 v_{2i} = m_1 v_{1f} + m_2 v_{2f}$$

For an elastic collision (restitution = 1.0), kinetic energy is also conserved.  
For a perfectly inelastic collision (restitution = 0.0), kinetic energy loss is maximized.

